Hungary  will lend 5 billion forint
($21 million) to unprofitable state-owned airline Malev Zrt.,
according to a government decision signed by Prime Minister
 Viktor Orban  and published in the  official gazette  yesterday.  The loan will be provided by MNV Zrt., the state asset
management company, according to the document.  Hungary is talking with potential European investors about
Malev after Chinaâ€™s Hainan Airlines withdrew from negotiations,
